            "text": "Welcome to our introduction to skewers! \n\nThe example is from one of our editor's games. Both players were rated around 2000 at the time. \n\nA skewer is a tactic in which two pieces that are lined up are attacked: the higher value piece is in front, and the lower value piece is on the same line behind it. When the higher value piece moves away, the attack on the lower value piece is exposed.",
